description:
**Position:** Director, IT Infrastructure & Support

**Location:** New York City Metro Area

**Salary:** $132,000 -$150,000



**Position Overview:**  

Project Renewal’s Director, IT Infrastructure & Support oversees the day-to-day management and support of IT infrastructure, including cloud services, servers, workstations, VoIP phone systems, Internet connections, firewalls, switches, mobile devices, and wireless access points. The position is actively engaged in the work of PRI’s programs, developing a deep understanding of workflows, staff roles, reporting requirements, and strategic objectives. The position oversees the day-to-day operations of both the IT helpdesk team and the network engineering team, ensuring the delivery if high-quality customer service and project delivery.



**Essential Duties & Responsibilities Include:**  

* Provide oversight for PRI’s IT helpdesk team to ensure proactive and high quality customer service to staff;
* Manage PRI’s network engineering team to maintain and constantly improve infrastructure;
* Regularly consult with PRI staff regarding technology needs and lead software requirements elicitation and documentation processes;
* Anticipate and research current and emerging organizational technology needs,
* Coordinate with CIO to proactively propose solutions, incorporating tools such as cost-benefit analysis, to current and emerging technology needs;
* Coordinate with vendors;
* Manage IT projects as assigned by the CIO, including:
* Developing coherent project plans, appropriate task assignments, and realistic time estimates for projects;
* Monitoring the overall progress of projects against plan, and regularly communicate project status to stakeholders;
* Identifying and managing project risk, project interdependency issues;
* Oversee and assist with the:
* Development of training and online reference materials;
* Development, review and execution of testing plans;
* Management of configurations and change process for IT infrastructure;
* Communicate with staff on a proactive basis regarding IT changes and incidents that affect them;
* Enforce information technology policies including ensuring adherence to funder requirements;
* Work on tasks and projects as assigned by supervisor.


**Qualifications:**  

* 10 years of IT infrastructure management;
* Working in an environment with regulatory IT compliance and security requirements;
* Working and communicating with senior management;
* Managing mix of on-premises, IaaS/SaaS, and Cloud-native IT operations;
* Leading the operations of mission critical systems and services;
* Supervising both IT helpdesk and network engineering functions;
* Designing and managing complex IT projects including multiple teams and vendors;
* Excellent written and verbal communication skills;
* Advanced technical experience designing and implementing solutions based on:
* Microsoft Hyper-V and Windows Server;
* Microsoft Azure (including AAD, virtual networks, virtual machines, web applications, SQL databases, VPNs);
* Microsoft 365 / Office 365; and
* Cisco Meraki firewalls, switches and WAPs


All newly hired Project Renewal staff must provide verification of being fully vaccinated against Covid-19.

**Bartender**



Reports to: Director of Restaurants


FLSA Status: Exempt


Location: L’Amico; The Vine

 **Job Overview:**



Chef Laurent Tourondel is seeking a full-time Cashier for its restaurant operations at Eventi hotel. This is a great opportunity if you want to grow your career, and for the right candidate there is growth as our company opens more restaurant/projects. Please send cover letter or note with why you are the right candidate along with your resume. This is a full time management position. The company offers competitive salaries, full benefits, and possibilities for advancement.

 **Job Duties & Responsibilities**:

* Responsible for ensuring company policies and brand standards are followed.
* Responsible for optimizing profits by controlling labor costs.
* Responsible for training and developing new hourly team members.
* Responsible for reviewing schedule requests or obtaining proper coverage for scheduled shifts;
* Responsible for Increasing sales by ensuring guest satisfaction and prompt problem resolution.
* Responsible for maintaining an overall management style in accordance with our established best practices.
* Responsible for providing leadership and direction to all team members to ensure efficient operation.
* Responsible for preparing and presenting hourly team member reviews.
* Responsible for providing technically proficient service to all guests and for being their advocate throughout their LTH experience;
* Responsible for treating all co-workers in a respectful manner;
* Responsible for having thorough knowledge of and for being able to accurately and attractively describe all food and beverage products;
* Responsible for having thorough knowledge of LTH, its origin, and philosophy and enthusiastically offering to share that knowledge with all guests;

 **Requirements**:

* Five years of prior experience in the food service industry;
* Two years of experience in a management role;
* Must be proficient in Micros for both front and back of house;
* Must have ability to accurately handle money, make change, process credit card transactions and have strong menu knowledge;
* DOH Food Handler’s Certification;
* Strong service background;
* Strong communication skills;
* Comfort in a high-paced/high-volume environment;
* Solid work ethic; able to lead by example with a can-do attitude;
* Ability to stand, sit, bend, kneel, and reach with little to no accommodations needed for possible extended periods of time;
* Able to carry/hold more than 10 lbs.



I acknowledge I have received, reviewed, and fully understand the job description for the Server – The Vine position. I further understand that I am responsible for the satisfactory execution of the essential functions described herein and under any conditions, as described.



